parameters.jsCode:
// [NDA SUMMARY] Hard eligibility guard - filters rows before classification.
// - BATCH_SIZE=12 per run
// - Skips rows that already have a category
// - Skips rows in 'category_processing' state (prevents double-processing)
// - Deduplicates by email or website
// - Requires at least company_name or website to be present
// Returns at most BATCH_SIZE eligible rows with row_id attached.

// [NDA SUMMARY] STAGE 1: Fast Keyword Classifier (< 5ms per lead)
// Builds a haystack from company_name + domain. Checks against ~50+ industry
// keywords (e.g., "solar", "photovoltaic", "renewable", "inverter", "battery storage").
// Uses tokenized matching for short keywords, substring for longer ones.
// If keyword found: sets classification_decision='final', category='[Category]'.
// If not found: returns unmodified for next stage.
// Returns classification_stage='keyword', classification_reason_detail with matched keyword.

// [NDA SUMMARY] STAGE 2a: Builds a clean homepage URL from the website field.
// Handles: missing protocol, www prefix, query strings, fragments.
// Uses URL parser with fallback string manipulation.

// [NDA SUMMARY] STAGE 2b: Extracts metadata from scraped HTML.
// - Parses <title> tag (first 300 chars)
// - Parses <meta name="description"> (first 500 chars)
// - Strips <script>, <style>, <nav>, <footer> blocks
// - Extracts visible body text (first 500 chars)
// - Combines into scraped_text (first 1000 chars)
// Sets scrape_succeeded=true if any metadata was found.

// [NDA SUMMARY] STAGE 2c: Post-Scrape Keyword Classifier
// Same keyword matching logic as Stage 1, but runs against scraped_text
// (title + description + body snippet) instead of just company name.
// If scrape failed or no keywords found: passes to Stage 3 (Gemini).

values.content:
=[NDA] Classify company based on metadata:
Company: {{company_name}}
Title: {{homepage_title}}
Description: {{homepage_description}}
Text: {{body_snippet}}
Return ONLY one label: [Category] or not_[category]related

parameters.jsCode:
// [NDA SUMMARY] STAGE 3b: Normalizes Gemini's output.
// Extracts text from various Gemini response formats (output, text, response,
// mergedResponse, candidates[0].content.parts).
// Checks for exact label match ('solar' or 'notsolarrelated').
// Sets classification_stage='ai', classification_decision='final'.
// Records classification_reason_detail for audit trail.

// [NDA SUMMARY] Finalizer: assembles the update payload for Baserow.
// Sets: category (from classifier), category_classified_at (ISO timestamp),
// category_classifier_reason (which keyword/why), processed='category_classified'.
// Preserves existing fields, deletes temporary classification metadata fields.
